WIDGET SELECTION GUIDE
When to use which widget:
Need                                   Use	                                   Why
Simple box with styling    	      Container	                         All-in-one solution
Just spacing	                     SizedBox	More performant
Inset spacing                     	Padding	Semantic clarity
Horizontal arrangement               	Row	Linear layout
Vertical arrangement	       Column	Linear layout
Overlapping widgets            	Stack	Layer multiple widgets
Dynamic space distribution	       Expanded/Flexible	Fill available space
Scrollable content	ListView/GridView	Performance with many items
Text display	Text/RichText	Styling options
Images	Image.network/asset	Multiple sources
User input	TextField/Form	Validation, controllers
Navigation	AppBar/Drawer/TabBar	Standard patterns
Theming	ThemeData	Consistency
Common Patterns:
dart
// Card pattern
Card(
  child: Padding(
    padding: EdgeInsets.all(16),
    child: Column(
      crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.start,
      children: [
        Text('Title', style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.headline6),
        SizedBox(height: 8),
        Text('Description'),
      ],
    ),
  ),
)

// List item pattern
ListTile(
  leading: CircleAvatar(backgroundImage: NetworkImage(url)),
  title: Text('Item Title'),
  subtitle: Text('Item Subtitle'),
  trailing: Icon(Icons.arrow_forward),
  onTap: () {},
)

// Form field pattern
TextFormField(
  decoration: InputDecoration(
    labelText: 'Field',
    border: OutlineInputBorder(),
    filled: true,
  ),
  validator: (value) => value!.isEmpty ? 'Required' : null,
)
